original: Ahlin, Erik Folke, tandläkare, Skövde, f. 15/10/99 i Vadstena av G. E. Ahlin o. Frida OMsson. G. 44 m. Gulle Hedlund f. Neikter. Barn: Lena f. 46. — Stud:ex. i Linköp. 21, med. kand. i Upps. 27, tandläkare 31. Assist. i Karlskrona 31-32, numera förest. f. Skövde tandklinik.
translated: Ahlin, Erik Folke, dentist, from Skövde, born on October 15, 1899 in Vadstena to parents G.E. Ahlin and Frida Olofsson. Married in 1944 to Gulle Hedlund (formerly Neikter). They have one child, Lena, born in 1946. Erik graduated from high school in Linköping in 1921, received his Bachelor of Medicine degree in Uppsala in 1927, and became a dentist in 1931. He was an assistant in Karlskrona from 1931-1932, and is currently in charge of the Skövde dental clinic.
